  <roomsDescription><![CDATA[<p><strong>North-facing</strong> <strong>twin rooms</strong> are around 28<span>m²</span> and have a bath. These rooms can sleep up to three (murphy bed).</p>
<p><strong>South-facing</strong> <strong>twin rooms</strong> are around 28<span>m² and have bath and a balcony. The third bed is a rollaway bed.</span></p>
<p><strong>Junior Suites</strong> are around 35<span>m² and have a lounge area with murphy bed that can sleep a third guest. These rooms also have a balcony are south-facing.</span></p>
<p><span><strong>Single rooms</strong> are around 18m² with bath and are either north or south-facing. South-facing singles are on request so please call us to book these.</span></p>
<p><strong>Two-bedroom suites</strong> are around <span>100m² and sleep 2 to 4 people. They have two bedrooms with en suite bathrooms (one with a shower and one with a bath), a living room and a south facing balcony or terrace with a view of the Eigers north face. They're located in the Grand Chalet annex building. Suites are available on request, please call to book. </span></p>
<p><span><strong>Three-bedroom suites</strong> are around 130m² and sleep 4 to 6 people. They have three-bedrooms with en suite bathrooms (one with a bath and two have showers), a living room and a balcony or terrace with views of the Eiger. They're located in the Grand Chalet annex building. Suites are available on request, please call to book.</span></p>
<p><strong>Room facilities:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Cable/satellite TV</li>
<li>Nespresso machines for coffee and tea</li>
<li>Safe</li>
<li>Mini bar</li>
<li>Hair dryer</li>
<li>Wi-Fi</li>
<li>Bathroom with bathtub</li>
<li>Cots available free of charge</li>
</ul>]]></roomsDescription>
